HEADWORD: zebra-tailed lizard
<hw>ze"bra-tailed liz`ard</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A lizard having a long
tail with black bands (<spn>Callisaurus draconoides</spn>), which lives
in the deserts of the southwestern U. S. and Mexico; called also
<altname>gridiron-tailed lizard</altname>.</def> <au>RHUD</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

